                                            Create playlists in seconds with this integration.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Spotify has just announced that it has partnered with ChatGPT to allow its users to create playlists and get personalized recommendations. Amid its arsenal of improving, built-in AI features, this move is a big step for the music streaming platform.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 08 Oct 2025 18:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/how-to-connect-and-use-chatgpt-with-spotify/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[An Open Source Phone Is the Free Software Foundation's Next Project]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/the-free-software-foundation-is-making-an-open-source-phone/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/ubuntu-touch.jpg" length="586" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Open Source]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Let's hope they finish this one.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The Free Software Foundation (FSF) is starting a new project called LibrePhone. Announced during the FSF's 40th birthday celebration earlier this month, this initiative is to build a mobile platform starting right from the firmware all the way up to the operating system.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 08 Oct 2025 17:36:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/the-free-software-foundation-is-making-an-open-source-phone/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Why I'm Buying the Pixel 8 Pro Instead of the Pixel 10]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/why-im-buying-the-pixel-8-pro-instead-of-the-pixel-10/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jordan Gloor]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/10/person-holding-up-the-back-of-a-blue-google-pixel-8-pro-phone.jpg" length="192" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Pixel 8 Pro]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Pixel 10]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            I'm an early adopter, but even I have my limits.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>I've relied on Google Pixel phones exclusively for the past four years, and after the release of the Pixel 10 last month, I decided it was time to upgrade models. I'm not going for the latest release, though.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 08 Oct 2025 16:45:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/why-im-buying-the-pixel-8-pro-instead-of-the-pixel-10/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[HMD’s Touch 4G Might Be the Dumbphone You Want]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/hmd-touch-4g-is-a-dumb-phone-with-some-smarts/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Cory Gunther]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/hmd-touch-4g-main.jpg" length="1001" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apps & Web Apps]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            A small, basic phone with USB-C and a headphone jack. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Do you ever find yourself wishing for a smartphone that wasn't so smart? One free of all the distractions of apps, social media, and endless notifications? Basic "dumb" phones still exist, and you can get modern features like a solid design and a touchscreen. That's where the all-new HMD Touch 4G comes in.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 08 Oct 2025 16:43:50 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/hmd-touch-4g-is-a-dumb-phone-with-some-smarts/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This Lenovo Tab on Sale Is a Great Fire Tablet Alternative]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/the-lenovo-tab-one-drops-to-its-lowest-price-ever/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/lenovo-tab-one-showing-a-game-where-someone-races-a-court-on-a-track.jpg" length="311" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><category><![CDATA[Deals]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            It has the Google Play Store, and it's at the lowest recorded price yet.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Today, you can grab the Lenovo Tab One for a surprisingly low price of just <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0F1NHSFMF?tag=hotoge-20&ascsubtag=UUhtgUeUpU2017193&asc_refurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.howtogeek.com%2Fthe-lenovo-tab-one-drops-to-its-lowest-price-ever%2F&asc_campaign=Affiliate" rel="noopener noreferrer sponsored nofollow" target="_blank" class="norewrite noskim">$100 on Amazon</a>. This is an impressive 19% discount off the usual $123.00 listed price.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 08 Oct 2025 16:41:24 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/the-lenovo-tab-one-drops-to-its-lowest-price-ever/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[9 Ways I Optimized My Linux PC for Gaming (Without Bazzite)]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/ways-i-optimized-my-linux-pc-for-gaming/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/52748617632_95b6e6bd29_o.jpg" length="275402" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[video games]]></category><category><![CDATA[PC Gaming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            You can upgrade your Linux by making a few new habits.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Turning your average Linux installation into a gaming powerhouse isn't exactly a one-click process, but I can tell you it's incredibly rewarding. It means you've got to dig deep into how your system is set up, understand the tricky bits of how your hardware talks to the software, and really take advantage of the insane flexibility that Linux offers.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 08 Oct 2025 16:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/ways-i-optimized-my-linux-pc-for-gaming/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Firefox Is Finally Letting You Separate Your Browsing Data]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/firefox-is-finally-letting-you-separate-your-browsing-data/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Arol Wright]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/firefox2.jpg" length="164" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Web]]></category><category><![CDATA[Firefox]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Long-overdue.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Profiles are a good way to manage separate browsing data for each digital footprint you might have—you can have a work one, a study one, or a personal one, or maybe even all three, so the browsing data from one doesn't mistakenly mix with the other. Now, Firefox is finally getting them. A bit later than most other browsers, but better late than never.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 08 Oct 2025 16:17:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/firefox-is-finally-letting-you-separate-your-browsing-data/</guid></item></channel>
